messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
We have an emergency here.
What's the hazard?
I just got burned by gasoline, please, hurry up.
I can't hear you clearly. Can you speak up?
I'm burnt. All my body was covered in gasoline. Please send an ambulance, quickly.
Okay, I'm trying to get help to you, but you need to calm down and tell me exactly what's going on.
Please get help out here. I am burning and it hurts so much.
What happened to you?
I was near my brother and gasoline spilled on me and I caught fire.
Okay, stay with me. Can you hang on while I get rescue for you?
Yes.
Okay, hang on, and please don't hang up, okay?
Are you still there?
Yes, I'm here.
What address is the patient at?
Pearson, yes, and Pearson.
What's going on there?
I got burnt by gasoline. I need help right now.
Okay, I have help on the way. How old are you?
And you said you were burned by gasoline?
Yes, all my body is covered in gasoline. I need to be rushed to a hospital right now.
Okay. Where are you burned?
Everywhere. All my body, my face is burnt.
Your whole body is burned?
Yes, I need an ambulance.
They are on the way. I need to get more information for the responders. Did you accidentally pour gasoline on yourself?
No, my brother was involved. There was gasoline and I caught on fire.
So you did catch on fire?
Yes, my whole body caught on fire.
Okay. Stay with me. What's the nearest intersecting road near you?
Pernado Street.
What's the exact address you're at?
I'm on Pearson Street, near Pernado.
Are you in front of a house?
Yes, I'm in front of a house.
Can you give me the phone number you're calling from?
Yes, it's [caller gives phone number].
Okay, I have help on the way. Do you want me to stay on the phone with you until they get there?
Yes, please.
Okay, stay on the line. Has anyone there been drinking tonight?
No.
Did she just spill the gasoline or did she catch on fire as well?
Fire and gasoline maybe.
Is she on fire right now?
She doesn't speak a lot of English.
Okay, I have help on the way. Do you need me to stay on the phone until the paramedics get there?
Yes.
They've been on the way since you called, okay?
Okay.
If anything changes, call us back. Help is on the way.
Thank you.
